<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<head>
	<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="about.css" />
</head>
<body>
	<div id="aboutPageContainer">
		<h2>krdwrd basics</h2>
		For you to be a productive drone, all you need to do is:
		<ul>
			<li>
				<b>Select a corpus</b> using the krdwrd menu in your status bar. A random page will be grabbed for you.
			</li>
			<li>
				<b>Annotate</b>
				the entire page by hovering over the content. Use the context menu to annotate
				the highlighted block.	Its color will change accordingly.
			</li>
			<li>
				<b>Submit</b>
				your annotation. A new page will be grabbed automatically.
			</li>
			<li class="info">
    		    Please note the keyboard shortcuts given next to the menu
        		items. They tend to make life a lot easier.
			</li>
		</ul>
		<br />
		Also check the <a href="https://krdwrd.org/trac/wiki/AnnotationGuidelines">Annotation Guidelines</a> on the krdwrd website.

		<h2>krdwrd utils</h2>

		The status bar pop-up offers some additional functionality:

		<ul>
            <li class="warn">
                Warning: These commands are highly experimental.
            </li>
			<li>
				<b>Propagate</b> traverses the document and moves annotations downwards to the leaf nodes.
			</li>
			<li>
				<b>Show Text</b> extracts all text from the current page and displays it in the sidebar, together with 
				the usual color annotation.
			</li>
			<li>
				<b>Design Mode</b> allows editing the current page.
				Please do not use this on corpus data, as your submission will be rejected.
			</li>
		</ul>
	</div>
</body>
